header.gameNote: CHICAGO INVITATIONAL CHALLENGE AT HOFFMAN ESTATES IL

article.headline: UMKC 64, Wofford 58
article.story: HOFFMAN ESTATES, Ill. -- Reggie Chamberlain scored 22 points and made eight free throws in the final 58 seconds of overtime to lead UMKC to a 64-58 victory against Wofford in the Chicago Invitational Challenge on Friday. Trinity Hall added 16 points and Estan Tyler eight points and six rebounds for the Kangaroos (2-4). Tyler's 3-pointer helped UMKC build a five-point lead in overtime, and Chamberlain protected it at the line. Brad Loesing scored 20 points and Lee Skinner 13 for the Terriers (2-3). Chamberlain was vital in forcing the extra period, scoring the last four points of regulation on two free throws and a layup to knot the score at 49-49.
